item.title: If you aren't retarted you know that the egg came first
item.dc:creator: @Omfgurweird Omfgurweird
item.description:
@Omfgurweird wrote:

Yeah, you just have to think about it. Everything evolved from cells and organisms of some sort. Over billions of years, they evolve into certain species. Now, there would only be a few mamals to begin with, but over time they would have to begin breeding amungst each other.

How can this be if they are different type of mamals?

Well, they would all be very similar to each other at the beginning, so it wouldn’t be like a horse trying to have a baby with a penguin. Then, they would eventualy branch out, creating hundreds and thousands of different mamals. This would be where they start evolving to they’re needs. So naturaly after awhile, they wouldn’t be able to breed with these other certain mamals, because they would have evolved so different. Now back to the chicken. After all that happened, the chicken would have finaly been created, and it IS possible that the mamal that it evolved from layed eggs. So if it did, then the egg came first. But if the mamal DIDN’T lay eggs. Then it would have had to be the chicken.

So in conclusion, for something to lay eggs, it wouldn’t just overnight start laying them instead of giving birth to them like a human does. Therfore, it would have had to evolve from a mamal that laid eggs before it, hence the egg being first. Unless you want to link the chicken all the way back to the first couple of animals. Then It would be the chicken rofl

~GoD
